Description: Native Linux desktop client for Music Assistant
 Music Assistant Native is a desktop application for controlling
 Music Assistant, the open-source music library manager from the
 Home Assistant ecosystem.
 .
 Connect to your Music Assistant server and browse your unified
 music library, control playback on any connected speaker (Sonos,
 AirPlay, Chromecast, DLNA, Snapcast, etc.), and manage your play
 queue with a native Qt/Kirigami interface.
